{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AqcCExxbhZEcYbCw44J6Lf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Implementation History — 304-response-envelope\n2\t\n3\tIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\n4\tattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\n5\tof every iteration to understand prior context.\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## Iteration 0 — 2026-04-22T06:57:47Z — BLOCKED\n10\t- **Blocker**: Spec is still Draft. Run '/refine 304-response-envelope' to break down the checklist.\n11\t\n12\t## Iteration 1 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n13\t- **Item**: [contracts] Create `backend/src/contracts/api-envelope.ts` + unit tests.\n14\t- **Changes**:\n15\t  - Added `backend/src/contracts/api-envelope.ts` exporting envelope primitives (`ApiEnvelopeSuccess`, `ApiEnvelopeError`, `ApiEnvelope`, `ApiError`), zod schemas (`ApiErrorSchema`, `ErrorEnvelopeSchema`, `envelope(dataSchema)`), and helpers `ok(c, data, status?)` / `err(c, status, code, message, opts?)`.\n16\t  - `ApiErrorCode` temporarily typed as `string`; will be narrowed to the `API_ERROR_CODES` union when `api-errors.ts` is rewritten in the next iteration.\n17\t  - Added `backend/src/__tests__/api-envelope.test.ts` — 26 tests covering success serialization (200/201/202), error serialization for all nine declared error statuses (400/401/403/404/409/422/429/500/503), schema round-trips, and discriminated-union parsing.\n18\t- **Verification**:\n19\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n20\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n21\t  - `pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/api-envelope.test.ts` → 26/26 passed\n22\t  - Full unit suite (`pnpm test:unit:self`) → 205/205 passed, 18 files\n23\t\n24\t## Iteration 1 — 2026-04-22T09:15:17Z — OK\n25\t- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n26\t\n27\t## Iteration 2 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n28\t- **Item**: [contracts] Rewrite `backend/src/contracts/api-errors.ts` to export `API_ERROR_CODES` + `ApiErrorCode` type; keep legacy helpers for the cleanup iteration; add a unit test.\n29\t- **Changes**:\n30\t  - Rewrote `backend/src/contracts/api-errors.ts`: added the `API_ERROR_CODES` constant (34 codes from FR-2) and derived `ApiErrorCode = (typeof API_ERROR_CODES)[keyof typeof API_ERROR_CODES]`. Kept legacy exports (`errorMessage`, `structuredErrorMessage`, `ErrorResponseBody`, `StructuredErrorResponseBody`, `StructuredErrorDetail`) intact — they are still consumed by 10 route files and the OpenAPI hook, and will be deleted in the cleanup iteration.\n31\t  - Narrowed `ApiErrorCode` in `backend/src/contracts/api-envelope.ts` from the temporary `string` alias to a re-export of the catalog-derived union. `err()` callers are now type-checked against the catalog.\n32\t  - Added `backend/src/__tests__/api-errors.test.ts` — 5 tests asserting the catalog is the single source of truth: every key equals its value, values are SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE, values are unique, the type derives correctly, and every FR-2 code is present.\n33\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/api-envelope.test.ts` to use a real catalog code (`NOT_FOUND`) in the generic error-status test instead of the placeholder `\"SOME_CODE\"` string literal (now rejected by the narrowed type).\n34\t- **Verification**:\n35\t  - `tsc --noEmit` → exit 0\n36\t  - `eslint src ...` → exit 0\n37\t  - Targeted: `vitest run src/__tests__/api-errors.test.ts src/__tests__/api-envelope.test.ts` → 31/31 passed\n38\t  - Full unit suite (`vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 210/210 passed across 19 files\n39\t\n40\t## Iteration 2 — 2026-04-22T09:20:18Z — OK\n41\t- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n42\t\n43\t## Iteration 3 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n44\t- **Item**: [openapi] Update `invalidRequestHook` in `backend/src/openapi/hono.ts` to return `422` envelope with `VALIDATION_FAILED` + Zod issue list; add hook test.\n45\t- **Changes**:\n46\t  - Rewrote `backend/src/openapi/hono.ts`: hook now accepts `{ success: true } | { success: false; error: z.ZodError }`, returns `err(c, 422, API_ERROR_CODES.VALIDATION_FAILED, \"Invalid request\", { retryable: false, details: result.error.issues })`. Removed legacy `errorMessage` import (will be deleted in cleanup iteration).\n47\t  - Added `backend/src/__tests__/openapi-invalid-request-hook.test.ts` — 4 tests: 422 status + VALIDATION_FAILED envelope + retryable:false; Zod issue list includes all failing paths; body round-trips through `ErrorEnvelopeSchema`; valid requests still succeed.\n48\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts` — two tests that asserted 400 + `{ error: \"Invalid request\" }` now assert 422 + envelope shape (the `/auth/challenge` route converts in a later iteration; only the hook-level assertion changed).\n49\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/leaderboard.test.ts` — same assertion shift for the legacy game-alias test.\n50\t- **Verification**:\n51\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n52\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n53\t  - `pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts` → 214/214 passed (20 files, +4 new hook tests)\n54\t\n55\t## Iteration 3 — 2026-04-22T09:25:50Z — OK\n56\t- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n57\t\n58\t## Iteration 4 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n59\t- **Item**: [middleware] Convert `backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts` to return `401 { ok: false, error: { code: \"AUTH_REQUIRED\", ... } }` envelopes; update `auth.test.ts` assertions.\n60\t- **Changes**:\n61\t  - Rewrote `backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`: replaced three `c.json({ error: ... }, 401)` call sites with `err(c, 401, API_ERROR_CODES.AUTH_REQUIRED, <message>)`. Imported `err` from `../contracts/api-envelope.js` and `API_ERROR_CODES` from `../contracts/api-errors.js`. Renamed the `catch (err)` binding to `catch (verifyError)` to avoid shadowing the imported helper.\n62\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/auth.test.ts`: the four 401 rejection tests now assert envelope shape (`body.ok === false`, `body.error.code === \"AUTH_REQUIRED\"`) in addition to status. The two message-specific tests assert the exact message for the two distinct 401 paths (\"Missing or invalid Authorization header\" and \"Invalid or expired token\").\n63\t  - `auth-routes.test.ts` intentionally left unchanged: its 401 cases come from the auth routes themselves (challenge/verify/refresh), not the JWT middleware. Those routes are converted in a later iteration (per checklist) — updating them now would break tests against still-legacy route handlers.\n64\t- **Verification**:\n65\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n66\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n67\t  - `pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts` → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n68\t\n69\t## Iteration 4 — 2026-04-22T09:28:56Z — OK\n70\t- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n71\t\n72\t## Iteration 5 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n73\t- **Item**: [middleware] Convert `backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` to `429` envelope with `RATE_LIMITED` code; update `rate-limit.test.ts` to assert envelope body.\n74\t- **Changes**:\n75\t  - Rewrote `backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`: both 429 call sites (global-limit and per-identity-limit) now use `err(c, 429, API_ERROR_CODES.RATE_LIMITED, \"Too many requests\", { retryable: true, details: { retryAfterMs: config.windowMs } })`. `Retry-After` header is preserved. Imported `err` from `../contracts/api-envelope.js` and `API_ERROR_CODES` from `../contracts/api-errors.js`.\n76\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts`: the per-wallet 429 test and the global 429 test now assert the full envelope body (`{ ok: false, error: { code: \"RATE_LIMITED\", message, retryable: true, details: { retryAfterMs } } }`). The 30-second-window test also asserts `details.retryAfterMs === 30_000`. Retry-After header assertions preserved.\n77\t- **Verification**:\n78\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n79\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n80\t  - `pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts` → 7/7 passed\n81\t  - Full unit suite (`pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n82\t\n83\t## Iteration 5 — 2026-04-22T09:32:36Z — OK\n84\t- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n85\t\n86\t## Iteration 6 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n87\t- **Item**: [routes] Convert `backend/src/routes/auth.ts` to envelope responses; update `auth-routes.test.ts`.\n88\t- **Changes**:\n89\t  - Rewrote all four auth routes in `backend/src/routes/auth.ts`:\n90\t    - `POST /challenge`: success → `ok(c, { nonce, message, expiresAt })`; declared 200 response now uses `envelope(ChallengeNonceResponseSchema)`; legacy 400 replaced with `422 ErrorEnvelopeSchema` (matches real hook behavior from iteration 3).\n91\t    - `POST /verify`: success → `ok(c, tokens)`; 401 errors use `err(c, 401, INVALID_SIGNATURE | CHALLENGE_EXPIRED, ...)`; the 500 profile-establish path uses `PRECONDITION_FAILED` (closest catalog fit for \"required state couldn't be established\"); declared 400/500 schemas replaced with `ErrorEnvelopeSchema`, added `422 ErrorEnvelopeSchema`.\n92\t    - `POST /refresh`: success → `ok(c, tokens)`; all three 401 paths (invalid, reuse, expired) use `err(c, 401, REFRESH_TOKEN_INVALID, ...)`; 400 replaced with `422 ErrorEnvelopeSchema`.\n93\t    - `POST /logout`: unchanged — still returns `204` with no body.\n94\t    - Removed `ErrorResponseSchema` import (kept `ChallengeNonceResponseSchema` + `TokenResponseSchema` as the inner data schemas inside `envelope(...)`).\n95\t  - Updated `backend/src/contracts/api-envelope.ts` to unblock route handler typing:\n96\t    - Added overload signatures on `ok<T>(c, data)` → `ok<T, S>(c, data, status)` so the handler return type narrows to the specific `200 | 201 | 202` literal the route declared (TypeScript inference would otherwise widen to the `SuccessStatus` union and fail the hono-zod-openapi `Handler` constraint).\n97\t    - Made `err<S extends ErrorStatus>(c, status, code, message, opts?)` generic on status for the same reason.\n98\t    - Introduced `ApiErrorDetails = any` alias for `ApiError.details` and `err(opts.details)`. Hono's `TypedResponse` narrows `unknown` to `JSONValue` in the inferred route response, which caused a type mismatch against a fully-typed `unknown`. `any` is the pragmatic fit — runtime values remain JSON-serializable (Zod issues, limits, etc.) and the schema-level `z.unknown().optional()` is unchanged.\n99\t    - Added `/* eslint-disable no-redeclare, no-undef */` around the overloaded `ok`/`err` block (overloads trigger base `no-redeclare`; `Response` intersection type triggers `no-undef` since ESLint doesn't know the global). typescript-eslint's own no-redeclare is overload-aware but isn't enabled in the shared config.\n100\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts`:\n101\t    - Every success assertion now destructures `{ ok, data }` from the envelope.\n102\t    - 401 assertions now check `body.ok === false` and `body.error.code` equals the exact catalog code: `REFRESH_TOKEN_INVALID` (replay, post-logout, invalid-token), `INVALID_SIGNATURE` (wrong wallet, wrong signature), `CHALLENGE_EXPIRED` (already-used nonce).\n103\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/waitlist-contract.test.ts` `responseKeys` helper — added `unwrapEnvelope()` that detects an envelope `oneOf` variant with `ok: true` and descends into the `data` schema's properties. Non-enveloped legacy routes (referral/*, public-referral/*) still work via fall-through. This makes the waitlist-contract test pass for the auth routes right now and will keep passing as other routes convert in later iterations.\n104\t- **Verification**:\n105\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n106\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n107\t  - Targeted: `vitest run src/__tests__/auth-routes.test.ts src/__tests__/auth.test.ts src/__tests__/rate-limit.test.ts` → 22/22 passed\n108\t  - Targeted: `vitest run src/__tests__/api-envelope.test.ts src/__tests__/openapi-invalid-request-hook.test.ts src/__tests__/waitlist-contract.test.ts` → 71/71 passed\n109\t  - Full unit suite (`pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n110\t\n111\t## Iteration 6 — 2026-04-22T09:47:44Z — OK\n112\t- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n113\t\n114\t## Iteration 7 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n115\t- **Item**: [routes] Convert `backend/src/routes/referral.ts` to envelope responses; update `referral-routes.test.ts`.\n116\t- **Changes**:\n117\t  - Rewrote all nine referral routes in `backend/src/routes/referral.ts`:\n118\t    - `POST /code`: success → `ok(c, { code })`; `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`; `404 PROFILE_NOT_FOUND`; `409 CODE_ALREADY_SET` / `CODE_TAKEN` (with retryable:false); `500 PRECONDITION_FAILED`. Custom invalid-request hook now returns `422 INVALID_CODE` (was `400 INVALID_CODE`) and passes Zod issues in `details`.\n119\t    - `POST /apply`: success → `ok(c, { referrerUserId, benefit })`; `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`; `404 PROFILE_NOT_FOUND` / `CODE_NOT_FOUND`; **`409 SELF_REFERRAL`** (was 400) / `409 ALREADY_LINKED`; `422 INVALID_CODE` for invalid body (was 400); `500 PRECONDITION_FAILED`.\n120\t    - `GET /code`: success → `ok(c, { code: row?.code ?? null })`; `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`.\n121\t    - `GET /referrer`: success → `ok(c, { referrerUserId, referrerUsername, referrerCode, linkedAt })` with all-null empty-state; `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`; `500 PRECONDITION_FAILED`.\n122\t    - `GET /stats`: success → `ok(c, stats)` with zero-default fields; `401`; `500`.\n123\t    - `GET /referrals`: success → `ok(c, { items })`; `401`; `500`.\n124\t    - `GET /earnings`: success → `ok(c, { items, pagination })`; removed dead `INVALID_PARAMS` 400 branch (Zod `z.coerce.number().int().min(1).default(1)` guarantees non-NaN after validation, and the default 422 hook already covers invalid query params). `401`; `422`; `500`.\n125\t    - `POST /claim`: success → `ok(c, { claimId, amountLamports, status }, 202)` (preserves 202); `401`; `404 PROFILE_NOT_FOUND`; **`422 ZERO_BALANCE` / `422 BELOW_THRESHOLD`** (was 400); `500 PRECONDITION_FAILED`.\n126\t    - `GET /claim/:claimId`: success → `ok(c, {...})`; `401`; `404 CLAIM_NOT_FOUND` (both missing claim and wrong-owner cases); `500`.\n127\t  - All response schemas now use `envelope(SuccessSchema)` for 2xx and `ErrorEnvelopeSchema` for 4xx/5xx. Removed imports of `errorMessage`/`structuredErrorMessage`/`ErrorResponseSchema`/`StructuredErrorResponseSchema` from `api-errors.ts` and `validators.ts` (legacy helpers still live there for the cleanup iteration).\n128\t  - Inlined `EarningsResponseSchema` locally (was an inline `z.object(...)` in the route responses map).\n129\t  - Renamed `catch (err)` bindings to `catch (insertError|fetchError|claimError)` to avoid shadowing the imported `err` helper.\n130\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/referral-routes.test.ts`:\n131\t    - All success assertions destructure `body.data`, assert `body.ok === true`.\n132\t    - `POST /code` invalid-format tests: status 400 → 422.\n133\t    - `POST /apply` self-referral test: status 400 → 409, renamed to \"rejects self-referral with 409\".\n134\t    - `POST /apply` empty code test: status 400 → 422, renamed to \"rejects empty code with 422\".\n135\t    - `POST /claim` zero-balance / below-threshold / double-claim tests: status 400 → 422.\n136\t    - `GET /claim/:claimId` 404 assertions now check `body.error.code === \"CLAIM_NOT_FOUND\"`.\n137\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/waitlist-contract.test.ts` `arrayItemKeys` helper — now routes through `unwrapEnvelope` before descending into the array property, so envelope-wrapped list responses (now `GET /referrals`) match the waitlist contract.\n138\t- **Verification**:\n139\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n140\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n141\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/referral-routes.test.ts` → 29/29 passed\n142\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts src/__tests__/waitlist-contract.test.ts` → 41/41 passed\n143\t  - Full unit suite (`pnpm vitest run --config vitest.unit.config.ts`) → 214/214 passed across 20 files\n144\t\n145\t## Iteration 7 — 2026-04-22T09:56:24Z — OK\n146\t- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n147\t\n148\t## Iteration 8 — 2026-04-22 — DONE\n149\t- **Item**: [routes] Convert `backend/src/routes/public-referral.ts` to envelope responses; update `public-referral-routes.test.ts`.\n150\t- **Changes**:\n151\t  - Rewrote both public-referral routes in `backend/src/routes/public-referral.ts`:\n152\t    - `GET /code/:code`: success → `ok(c, { exists })` (200); invalid-format input still returns `200 { ok: true, data: { exists: false } }` (probe-style, per FR-7); failure path now uses `err(c, 500, PRECONDITION_FAILED, ...)`.\n153\t    - `GET /:identifier`: success → `ok(c, { userId, username, referralCode })` with nullable `referralCode`; missing profile returns `err(c, 404, NOT_FOUND, \"Profile not found\")`; failure path uses `err(c, 500, PRECONDITION_FAILED, ...)`.\n154\t    - 200 responses now declare `envelope(SuccessSchema)`; 404/500 declare `ErrorEnvelopeSchema`. Removed imports of `errorMessage` (from `api-errors.ts`) and `ErrorResponseSchema` (from `validators.ts`) — legacy helpers still live there for the cleanup iteration.\n155\t    - Renamed `catch (err)` bindings to `catch (lookupError)` in both handlers to avoid shadowing the imported `err` helper.\n156\t  - Updated `backend/src/__tests__/public-referral-routes.test.ts`:\n157\t    - Success assertions destructure `body.data` and assert `body.ok === true`.\n158\t    - 404 assertion now checks `body.error.code === \"NOT_FOUND\"` instead of the legacy `{ error: \"NOT_FOUND\" }` shape.\n159\t    - `/code/:code` equality assertions updated to the full envelope shape `{ ok: true, data: { exists } }`.\n160\t    - Dogpile passthrough test left unchanged (dogpile routes are converted in a later iteration).\n161\t- **Verification**:\n162\t  - `pnpm typecheck:self` → exit 0\n163\t  - `pnpm lint:self` → exit 0\n164\t  - Targeted: `vitest run --config vitest.integration.config.ts src/__tests__/